The paper deals with the verification of distributed algorithms, which is a topic in the field of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also introduces a logic for reasoning about processes and pids, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of automata-theoretic methods is also a prominent feature of the paper, which could place it in the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL) or formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the verification problem, which could also place it in the sub-category of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
